review_blob: Great hoppy IPA. Pretty disappointed that Ive been to pubs and "beer shops" on much of north island, NZ and no one had even heard of 8 wired until I got to Auckland. Anyway, great beer. Glad I finally found some in NZ.

This may just be the best beer Ive ever tasted. It is initially like many exceptional IPAs out there. Then the aftertaste kicks in and its something I cant quite describe, but it makes you want to take another drink immediately. SO GOOD. Is this the liquid version of crack?

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Pours opaque orange with a think white head that lasts. Aroma is kind of non-existent - maybe it was a bit too cold? Tastes good with decent amount of hops. Not as hoppy as the label makes it sound. Pliny or Blind Pig are way more hoppy. But it is quite drinkable and very good.

Pours thick black with a creamy light brown head that lasts. Smells like coffee and something slightly sweet light maybe molasses or jam. Tastes similar to the smell. A bit heavy on the alcohol taste, but overall real nice.
Poured thick black with a small dark head. Smells like coffee and oysters. Tastes heavy with a bit of bitterness/tang. Stellar beer.

Not sure how to describe this, but it tastes a bit more "green" than Pliny the Elder. I prefer Pliny to this, but that does not mean much as I prefer Pliny to just about anything. This is quite a good IPA and lacking Pliny, I would take this in a heartbeat.

Not bad. Not as sour as I was expecting. Pour was aber with a nice head that lasted. With the prominent labeling of the use of brett and with the "wild" in the name, I was expecting something a bit more exotic. So maybe the tameness was just due to expectations. Either way, its a decent beer. Would drink again.

Initial reaction: wow. Pours oily black with a tan head that will hang around for a bit if you can get it. The coffee is immediate, but silky chocolate is right behind it and lasts. The alcohol is surprisingly almost non-existant - at 12%, youd expect much more. This is a dangerous beer.

Just an excellent beer. If I was trapped on a desert island and could only bring one beer with me for the rest of my life, this would probably have to be it. Easy to drink, tastes great. Great hops, but not too hoppy.
Very good Belgian style ale. I might be grading it a bit low, because Im into stouts at the moment and I really wanted Consecration, but had to settle for Damnation!

For as much as I love the Mirror Pond Pale Ale, I cannot believe I have never had this before. This beer is absolutely stellar. The coffee colored head does not last long, but the aroma and taste are outstanding.

Just an outstanding beer. The aroma is full cherries. The taste is complex is the perfect combination of tartness and sweetness. The palate is almost like a light syrup. Excellent. Possibly my favorite beer.
Very good beer. Tastes a little like a great Mikkeller beer thats been watered down or mixed with something else.
beer_name: Stillwater / Mikkeller Two Gypsies Our Side

review_blob: I had this with some oysters - I dont know if it was the oysters or the tabasco, but this beer was tasting like apple cider. In a good way.
